## Advanced Configuration Scenarios

This article extends the concepts introduced in ART-901 and provides sample code for complex setups.

### Dynamic Configuration Reload

Use the `config.watch()` API to hot-reload configuration without restarting:

```javascript
widget.config.watch('/etc/widget/config.d/', (change) => {
  widget.reloadConfig(change.file);
});
```

### Custom Config Plugins

Implement the `IConfigPlugin` interface to extend the configuration flow with custom sources:

```javascript
class MyRemoteConfigPlugin implements widget.config.IConfigPlugin {
  load() { return fetch('/api/config').then(r => r.json()); }
  validate(data) { return schema.validate(data); }
}
widget.config.use(new MyRemoteConfigPlugin());
```

### Configuration Flow with Multiple Sources

When multiple config sources (file, environment, remote) are used, define a merge strategy in the Widget boot sequence. The order of sources determines precedence.

